Hey hey,

Today, we're beyond excited to announce the release of the official Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki available at

[wiki.hypixel.net](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Main_Page)​

Have you ever wondered how often an item may drop or how a specific mechanic works in SkyBlock? We've got you covered!

Continue reading to learn more about the new Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki!

► What is the Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki?

[![](data:image/png;base64,)](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Main_Page)

Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki Main Page​

The Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki is Hypixel-led and community-maintained, which means that you're always going to get the most accurate information, as quickly as possible.

We have been working on this wiki for quite some time now and feel it is finally ready to be used by the public. However, please note that the Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki is currently in beta and unexpected issues and outages may arise!

As of release day, we cover all of the must-have SkyBlock knowledge, such as:

-   [Collections](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Collections)
-   [Dragons](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Ender_Dragon)
-   [Dungeons](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Dungeon)
-   [Pets](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Pets)
-   [The Hub](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Hub)
-   [Locations](https://wiki.hypixel.net/Locations)

-   ...and much, much more

► Our Goals

Accurate & Easily Accessible Information

Currently, a large chunk of information is gathered through various methods, such as testing or word-of-mouth. This method is not very accurate and often causes misinformation being spread.

Having an official Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki will mean that all the information will be hosted directly by the Hypixel team, making it easy to find what you are looking for.

Our goal is to provide the most accurate information in the best way possible. We will continually make improvements where needed and hope to provide the highest level of information transparency.

Quicker Release of Public Information

The plan with any SkyBlock update is to have basic pages ready on the day of release.

While you can look forward to these pages, please note that content such as secret quests or late-level unlocks won't be shown immediately as we don't want to take the sense of exploration and discovery away from the community.

► Future Plans

We are currently focusing on two major wiki-related projects:

-   Starting off, we plan on doubling the Wiki Editor Team, so keep an eye out for an official application process in the [SkyBlock forums](https://hypixel.net/categories/skyblock.194/) over the next coming weeks!
-   Also, we are preparing pages and information related to the upcoming release for the Nether island, so stay tuned for that!

► How can I help?

I found a bug!

At this time, you can help by reporting any issues you find related to the Hypixel SkyBlock Wiki, such as:

-   Incorrect information
-   Wrong images
-   Misspellings
-   Design & functional bugs
-   Accessibility barriers
-   etc.

Please use the official...

[Bug Report Form](https://hypixel.net/bug-reports/create#website)​

on this very website to help us squish any bugs you find! Please note that bug reports submitted directly to the Wiki Editors will be dismissed.

What about other games on the network?

The SkyBlock Wiki isn't where we want it to be quite yet, so we won't consider adding content for other games until the SkyBlock portion of the wiki is complete.

What about other languages?

Hypixel puts a heavy emphasis on localization through its support for 19+ languages to choose from in-game. Because of this, we are actively considering adding support for these languages at a later point in time. The wiki only supports English at this point in time.

As always, [report all bugs here](https://hypixel.net/bug-reports/create#website) so we can fix them as soon as possible! Additionally, we will also be listening to this thread for general feedback and suggestions.

We hope you enjoy browsing around the wiki!
